cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CR

This paper is about natural language understanding (NLU) systems and their ability to perform inductive reasoning from text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper evaluates the performance of different models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Learning), which deals with machine learning and statistical models. Additionally, the paper involves graph neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with neural networks and their applications. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the robustness of models, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with evaluating the security and robustness of systems.
